ebra)">basis</a> of the row space of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"=
font-style:italic;">A</span>. We claim that the vectors <span class=3D"texh=
tml"><i>A</i><b>x</b><sub>1</sub>, <i>A</i><b>x</b><sub>2</sub>, ..., <i>A<=
/i><b>x</b><sub><i>r</i></sub></span> are <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Linearly_independent" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Linearly indep=
endent">linearly independent</a>. To see why, consider a linear homogeneous=
 relation involving these vectors with scalar coefficients <span class=3D"t=
exhtml"><i>c</i><sub>1</sub>, <i>c</i><sub>2</sub>, ..., <i>c<sub>r</sub></=
i></span>:
